        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 9, "name": "Yext" },
        { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 10, "name": "Moz Local" }
      ]
    },
    {
      "@context": "https://schema.org",
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the best SEO tool for law firms in 2026?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For most firms, theStacc is the best all-in-one — it combines automated practice-area content with Google Business Profile management at $99–$167/mo. For local rank tracking, BrightLocal. For review management with text/email outreach, Birdeye. For free local visibility, every firm should claim and optimise Google Business Profile first." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Why do lawyers need different SEO tools?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Legal SEO is local-intent dominant, with extremely high keyword competition and strict YMYL content quality bars. Tools that work for ecommerce often miss on local pack visibility, citation consistency across legal directories (Avvo, Justia, FindLaw), and the review velocity required to win the map pack. Lawyer-specific stacks lean heavily on local + reputation tooling." }},
