        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Can a small law firm rank without an SEO agency?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — most solo and small firms over-pay for agencies that re-sell tools the firm could run directly. A $99/mo theStacc subscription plus a free Google Business Profile and a $39/mo BrightLocal account covers what most legal SEO retainers deliver at $1,500–$3,000/mo. Hire an agency for strategy and competitive verticals, not basic execution." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "What is the most important SEO factor for lawyers?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "For most practice areas, it is local pack visibility — the three-pack map result that drives free-consultation calls. That is won with a fully optimised Google Business Profile, consistent NAP across legal directories, a steady stream of recent positive reviews, and practice-area content that maps to client queries in your service area." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Does theStacc write content lawyers can actually publish?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes — theStacc is configured for practice-area SEO content (personal injury, family law, criminal defence, immigration, estate planning, etc.). Output is structured around client intent (FAQs, statutes, process explanations) rather than ranking-only fluff, and meets the editorial bar most firms hold for YMYL content. Attorneys keep a final review pass before high-stakes posts go live." }},
        { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is Birdeye or Google Business Profile better for managing reviews?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Both — start with Google Business Profile for the platform itself (free), and add Birdeye when you need outbound text/email review requests at scale. Most growth in star count and review velocity comes from systematic outreach after each matter closes, which is exactly what Birdeye and similar tools automate." }}
      ],
      "author": { "@type": "Person", "name": "Ritik Namdev", "url": "https://thestacc.com/authors/ritik-namdev/", "sameAs": ["https://www.linkedin.com/in/ritiknamdev/"] }
    }
  ]
